Generic Photo.Date: 30 August 2017 By: Viewed: 1267Two toddlers were burnt&nbsp;to death in a house fire on a farm in the Tshipise area that occurred on Tuesday, 29 August.According to information supplied by the police, both children, a 20-month-old baby and a three-year-old, were alone in their home on the farm Plaas Mount Stuart near Schuitdrift. The children were in the care of their mother when the fire broke out.Limpopo police spokesperson Lt-Col Moatshe Ngoepe said the mother was not at her house. &ldquo;She allegedly went to another house to cook food. While she was busy cooking, she heard neighbours screaming and calling her,&rdquo; said Ngoepe.The woman found her house consumed by flames. Both children&nbsp;burnt&nbsp;to death.&ldquo;The cause of this fire is unknown&nbsp;but will be further investigated,&rdquo; said Ngoepe. &nbsp;Email: More photos... 